            {
              "label": {
                "en": [
                  "Description"
                ]
              },
              "value": {
                "en": [
                  "A translation of an Arabic text into Mehri Recording likely to have been made during the 1967 expedition to Soqotra, of which Johnstone was a member. The expedition was led by Major P. G. Boxall, and sponsored by Admiral Sir Michael Le Fanu. The group comprised of civilian and service members, and included experts on languages, geology, entomology, botany, medicine, and archaeology, as well as military field survey teams of the Royal Navy and the Royal Engineers. They also conducted a coastal hydrographic survey [information from Doe 1992, which can be found at YK.1992.b.6319]. Recording date based on date of Boxhall's expedition to Soqotra. Information on contributors, and location recording is not described on the box, cassette, or documentation"
                ]
              }
            }
